ationsSupport for athletic operations gives VMI s coaches and athletic staff the resources they need to help cadet athletes fully achieve their athletic and leadership potential  FacilitiesThe cadet athletes who proudly represent VMI   and the coaches and staff members who serve them   deserve the best possible facilities for practice and competition  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  CAMPAIGN RESOURCES   Video   Campaign Cabinet   Policies VMI   Foundation   Alumni    Keydet Club UNCOMMON PURPOSE   In 1839  VMI set an uncommon course  to prepare young people for lives of service  leadership  and character  VMI cadets learn   through a rigorous military system  a demanding academic curriculum  and a robust athletic program  They leave VMI prepared to lead lives of strength  honor  and integrity   to serve their country and their communities as citizen soldiers  in times of peace and in times of deepest peril  THE CAMPAIGN FOR VMI Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7287 F  540 464 4545 give vmiaa org Support the Team  skip to content VMI Virginia Military Institute Website Shopping Cart Menu Home Why VMI Matters Priorities How you can help  Strengthen Academics Prepare Leaders Support the Team Provide Opportunity Believe in the Mission Preserve Our Legacy Get Involved About Giving Videos Stories Progress Give Close Menu Home Why VMI Matters Priorities How you can help  Strengthen Academics Prepare Leaders Support the Team Provide Opportunity Believe in the Mission Preserve Our Legacy Get Involved About Giving Videos Stories Progress Give Give to Athletics Athletics Gifts at Work Athletics Training is Training for Life   Why Give  Campaign Video Spirit of VMI Inspires Gift Robert Troxler  63  Jimmy Rogers  67 Austin Brockenbrough III Tom Slater  66 Walt Perrin II  62    Tom Slater s Success Started with VMI FootballRead why Tom Slater gives to VMI   Support the Team On and Off the Field VMI athletics is about shaping character  competing honorably  and forging stronger bonds within the VMI family  Cadets are given the opportunity to compete at the highest level of intercollegiate athletics while broadening their horizons through VMI s extraordinary education  More than one quarter of the Corps of Cadets is a member of the Institute s 18 NCAA Division I teams  however  because the Institute is one of the smallest Division I institutions  it lacks the resources that large schools have  Generous private giving  therefore  is essential if our athletic program is to continue in its mission  Both endowment and annual giving generate the operating support for VMI s athletic teams that allows coaches and staff to focus on developing cadets as athletes and leaders and to build competitive programs  Endowment and annual giving also provide grant in aid support to our cadet athletes  ScholarshipsGrant in aid support makes it possible for extraordinary young athletes to compete at the highest level of intercollegiate athletics while becoming extraordinary young leaders  OperationsSupport for athletic operations gives VMI s coaches and athletic staff the resources they need to help cadet athletes fully achieve their athletic and leadership potential  FacilitiesThe cadet athletes who proudly represent VMI   and the coaches and staff members who serve them   deserve the best possible facilities for practice and competition  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  CAMPAIGN RESOURCES   Video   Campaign Cabinet   Policies VMI   Foundation   Alumni    Keydet Club UNCOMMON PURPOSE   In 1839  VMI set an uncommon course  to prepare young people for lives of service  leadership  and character  VMI cadets learn   through a rigorous military system  a demanding academic curriculum  and a robust athletic program  They leave VMI prepared to lead lives of strength  honor  and integrity   to serve their country and their communities as citizen soldi